item.title: Mith Seeds
item.dc:creator: @runescape_sucks runescape sucks
item.description:
@runescape_sucks wrote:

[quote=“deathschaos9, post:2, topic:341719”][anchor=unreachable][size=15pt]Unreachable Statement[/size]
I thought I added that error, guess not. Anyway, an unreachable statement is a statement that comes after a break or return.

Here’s an example of an unreachable statement.

class Example { public static void main(String args[]) { if(args[0].equals("example")) { System.out.println("This is an example"); return; System.out.println("This is an unreachable statement"); } } }

An acceptable alternative would be something like.

class Example { public static void main(String args[]) { if(args[0].equals("example")) { System.out.println("This is an example"); return; } System.out.println("This is an unreachable statement"); } }[/quote]
